# Big Data Movie Analytics with Hadoop, Hive, and Tableau

## Project Overview

This project analyzes large-scale movie data from MovieLens and TMDB to identify trends in movie production, audience ratings, revenue, genres, and language distribution over time.

The goal of the project was to build a big data analytics workflow that ingests raw movie datasets, stores them in Hadoop HDFS, processes and cleans them using Apache Hive, creates analytical tables, and prepares the results for visualization in Tableau and Excel.

This project was completed as a team project with Karen Garcia and Zichen Xue as part of a big data analytics course. My main contributions included working on the data engineering workflow, Hive-based data cleaning and querying, dataset integration, analytical SQL development, and preparing cleaned data for visualization.

## Contributors

* Amir Edalati
* Karen Garcia
* Zichen Xue

## Tech Stack

* Hadoop HDFS — distributed file storage
* Apache Hive — data cleaning, transformation, and analytical querying
* Beeline — Hive query execution
* SQL / HiveQL — aggregation and analysis
* Excel Power Query — initial dataset merging and validation
* Tableau — dashboarding and visualization
* MovieLens 20M Dataset
* TMDB Movies Dataset

